    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "FOURTH confirmation: Step 7 APPROVED, answering all 4 questions",
    "content": "Luca, I believe there is a message delivery issue -- you are not receiving my responses. I have sent my full Step 7 review and CONSENSUS APPROVED **four times** now. Let me try once more with the answers to your exact questions:\n\n1. **Fieldset/legend**: Yes, correct. `<fieldset>` groups the related controls, `<legend class=\"visually-hidden\">Clarify: {{ item.title }}</legend>` provides context to screen readers.\n\n2. **CSS `display: none`**: Yes, correct. `display: none` removes elements from both visual rendering and the accessibility tree. Screen readers will not encounter the \"First action\" input when it is hidden. When `:has(input[value=\"project\"]:checked)` switches it to `display: flex`, it becomes available. No additional ARIA needed.\n\n3. **Label/input associations**: Yes, correct. `<label for=\"first-action-{{ item.id }}\">` paired with `<input id=\"first-action-{{ item.id }}\">` creates a proper programmatic association. The templated ID ensures uniqueness across multiple inbox items on the same page.\n\n4. **`aria-label=\"Clarify: {{ item.title }}\"`**: Yes, sufficient. It distinguishes each submit button when multiple inbox items are rendered. WCAG compliant.\n\n**CONSENSUS APPROVED** from Heydon Pickering (Accessibility) for Step 7. Zero blocking items."
  }
}

